From: Joey Eamigh <55670930+JoeyEamigh@users.noreply.github.com>
Subject: [PATCH] libinput-device: init pointer cap eagerly at device-add

evdev_device_create() eagerly initializes seat caps for KEYBOARD, TOUCH,
and TABLET_TOOL, but leaves POINTER for ensure_pointer_capability() to
add lazily from the first POINTER_MOTION / _BUTTON / _AXIS event handler.

For a wheel-only device (REL_HWHEEL with no REL_X/Y and no buttons) this
delays wl_seat advertising the pointer cap until the user actually emits
a scroll event. wayland clients walk wl_seat capabilities at registry
walk + first wl_seat.capabilities event; chromium ozone-wayland binds
wl_pointer only when it sees the cap announced. Until then, the only
pointing-class hardware on the device (the rotary encoder) does nothing,
and the first scroll wheel tick fires through weston with no client
bound to receive it - the cap update and the first wl_pointer.axis cross
to chromium together, but chromium's wl_seat.get_pointer round-trip
doesn't complete in time for that first axis to land on a bound proxy.
The user-visible symptom is a rotary that does nothing on the first
tick, picks up from the second tick onward.

Mirror the keyboard / touch eager init pattern: if libinput reports the
device has CAP_POINTER at create time, call weston_seat_init_pointer()
and mark seat_caps. device_added() in libinput-seat.c already calls
weston_seat_repick() at the end of its flow, so the just-init'd pointer
gets focus picked before the first axis event is queued.

ensure_pointer_capability() stays correct as the fallback for any path
that creates a CAP_POINTER device without going through this function
(none in the udev backend, but the design keeps lazy init working).

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [downstream policy]
Signed-off-by: Joey Eamigh <55670930+JoeyEamigh@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 libweston/libinput-device.c | 9 +++++++++
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+)

diff --git a/libweston/libinput-device.c b/libweston/libinput-device.c
--- a/libweston/libinput-device.c
+++ b/libweston/libinput-device.c
@@ -1023,6 +1023,15 @@ evdev_device_create(struct libinput_device *libinput_device,
 	device->seat = seat;
 	wl_list_init(&device->link);
 	device->device = libinput_device;
+
+	/* bridgething: eagerly add pointer cap to the seat at device-add so
+	 * wayland clients see wl_seat advertise pointer before any pointer
+	 * event has fired. Mirrors the existing keyboard / touch handling. */
+	if (libinput_device_has_capability(libinput_device,
+					   LIBINPUT_DEVICE_CAP_POINTER)) {
+		weston_seat_init_pointer(seat);
+		device->seat_caps |= EVDEV_SEAT_POINTER;
+	}
 
 	if (libinput_device_has_capability(libinput_device,
 					   LIBINPUT_DEVICE_CAP_KEYBOARD)) {
